Preheat your oven to 200°C, bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with
@salt{0.25%tsp}. Chop the @potatoes{450} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel).
Peel the @garlic cloves{2}. Trim the root from the @pak choi{1} and separate the
leaves. Halve the @plum{1}, remove the stone and chop the flesh of each plum
into 12 thin segments. Trim the @spring onion{1} and thinly slice.

Add the potatoes and the garlic clove to the boiling water and simmer until
tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in
your pan.

Meanwhile, pop a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil). Season the
@duck breasts{2} with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Once hot, lay the duck in the pan
skin-side down, fry until the skin is golden, ~{5%minutes}. Turn, cook for
~{1%minute} on the flesh side to seal the meat. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands
after handling raw meat and it's packaging. Transfer to a #baking tray{}
skin side up and roast on the top shelf of your oven until cooked,
~{10-12%minutes}.

Pop your frying pan back on medium high heat (no need to wash - you want the
lovely duck fat!). Add the plums to the pan and fry, turning them every minute
until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Pour in the @water{75} and add the
@sugar{1}, @chicken stock powder{1} and @hoisin sauce{25}. Bring to the boil
and simmer until thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}. TIP: Add a splash of water if it
thickens too much. Once cooked, set aside.

Once the duck is cooked, remove from your oven and rest in a warm place, covered
in #tin foil{}, for ~{5-7%minutes}. IMPORTANT: The duck is cooked when it is
no longer pink in the middle. Meanwhile pop your bok choy on your duck baking
tray (no need to wash) and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat
in the duck fat, arrange in in a single layer and roast in your oven until
tender, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Once the potatoes are cooked and back in their pan, add the spring onion along
with a knob of @butter{1%knob} and splash of @?milk{1%splash} (if you have it).
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and then mash with a #potato masher{}. Cover
with a #lid{} to keep warm. Reheat the plum sauce with a splash of water if you
need to. Thinly slice the duck and serve with the mash and bok choy alongside.
Spoon over the hoisin plum sauce and enjoy!